title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta 92G
postcontent:
Just bought this a few days ago, but happened upon a G19 this morning. So I have to get rid of one.

This is a Beretta 92G Police-trade-in that I bought at Bradis. 2005 manufacture date. Haven't even had a chance to fire it yet. Just took it home and cleaned it up. It does have standard police trade in type of wear. The 92G is really cool b/c while it looks the same as other 92s, the safety is a decocker only. Which means it has no manual safety. With it I have 2 magazines, a fobus paddle holster, and lock. Also, the cardboard box it came in. As big as this thing is, in the fobus holster I think this might be the most comfortable gun I've ever carried. Then again, this is the first time I've used one of those holsters, still very cool.

Anyway, I paid like $502 out the door so I'll start it at $460 OBO.

title: For Sale:  Star Modelo Super 9x23mm 1911
postcontent:
I have for sale a Star Modelo Super in 9x23 a.k.a. 9mm Bergmann Bayard. This pistol is in very good condition, with bright blueing as you can see. The barrel has some pitting. I have looked around online and others are asking around $400 for far inferior condition examples. I have fired over 500rds through this thing and had a hand full of misfires, due to the 50 year old ammo I was firing. It is an extremely accurate pistol and is outstanding for plinking. There is still a lot of surplus ammo available for dirt cheap. I believe I have a few hundred rounds left for it. It is in the pattern of a 1911, but for me has a much more comfortable feel and weight. Honestly it is my favorite plinker and is a blast to shoot. I realize the price is a little high, I was just kind of going off of what I saw online. Hit me up if your interested and I will entertain any serious offers. These are great little guns and I'm sure you will not be dissipointed. I believe this one was produced in 1952 and it is Spanish military proofed. 

Must have CCL, Permit to purchase, or C&R in hand.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Para PXT 1911 Single Stack SSP Regal
postcontent:
Good and Bads, and I will start with the bad. This gun was carried by prev owner and it shows. The Regal finish is well worn near the muzzle and there are some small scratches/marks here and there on the whole gun. The pics do a good job of showing them all. I can send more pics if you are picky about your 1911's. NO RUST and most the wear is on the slide. The two factory mags are 7 rounders. It has a factory full length guide rod but DOESN'T require any special tools to disassemble.

Now for the good. This is a very TIGHT 1911. There is barely any wiggle between frame and slide and when you shake it doesnt sound like a dog clicker.  Has the Para power extractor (PXT). Trigger on these SSP's is great and this one is no exception. The safety is not ambi but is serrated and extended making it very easier to operate. The slide release is also serrated and slightly longer than standard. The mainspring housing has a great checkering and the frame is made in a way that it just fits good in your hand. Novak style rear sight and dovetail front. These use the 3-dot system and are clean easy to see dots that make lining up targets quick and easy. The rear sight has rounded corners to prevent snagging on clothes. Rosewood grips have good checkering still (I think might have been removed for a different set when carried becuase they dont have much wear). 

I have shoot this with 150 rounds of FMJ and 50 rounds of WWB HP's since I have had it. No failure of any kind and shoot great. I will say I didnt do much crazy hard shooting or really try to see what it could do. I will say at 25 yards and less I can hit a 8" circle no problem even with rapid shots and if I try I get 2-3" groups easy. Pretty good since its a new pistol to me and I aint that great of a shot.

Everything appears factory except the Pearce finger grooved grip enhancement I just added new and the prev owner installed an Ed Brown barrel bushing. I will say this bushing is TIGHT but I was able to still turn it by hand (hurt my thumb a lil  ) to disassemble. 

Comes with 1911, 2x 7rnd factory mags, grip enhancement (already installed but can easily be removed if you like) and original box. I do not have the original manual but you can get it on Para's website.

ASKING $600 OBO and there is an ARGUNTRADER.COM Member Discount
